# Zoc AI — Next 6 Months Development Plan

> Horizon: 6 months from v2.0.0.
> Goal: turn the working v2.0.0 into a polished, daily-driver product with a real user base.
> Six focused monthly plans. One theme per month. Each month is shippable on its own.

---

## Month 1 — CI Distribution & Signed Installers

**Theme**: the v2.0.0 release pipeline already fails-hard without installers and produces real bundles on each host — now harden distribution. Build every OS in CI on every tag, sign + notarize, ship auto-updates.

### Deliverables
- CI matrix building Linux (x86_64 + arm64), macOS (Intel + Apple Silicon), Windows (x64) installers on every tagged release. (Task #10, #20)
- macOS notarization + Windows Authenticode signing wired into CI secrets. (Task #19)
- Auto-update endpoint live: `releases.llama.studio/updates/{target}/{arch}/{version}` serving signed Tauri update manifests.
- Crash reporting — opt-in Sentry (or self-hosted GlitchTip) for sidecar + Rust shell.
- Public download page (static site) with checksums + GPG signatures.

### Success criteria
- One-click install on all three OSes from a non-technical user's perspective.
- Auto-update works end-to-end on a real machine.
- < 60 min from `git tag` to all installers being downloadable.

---

## Month 2 — Onboarding & First-Run Quality

**Theme**: a first-time user with zero context is productive in under 5 minutes.

### Deliverables
- Guided onboarding tour: highlight the file tree, chat, terminal, command palette.
- Provider auto-detect: detect a running llama.cpp server, list loaded models, offer to download a recommended one with a progress bar.
- Embedding model picker in Settings (Task #14) + "Semantic search is on offline fallback" banner (Task #15).
- Workspace import: detect git repos, `.gitignore` is respected by the indexer out of the box.
- In-app splash + About screen with branding. (Task #18, currently cancelled — revive)
- Sample workspace: "Try a demo project" button that clones a small repo to scratch.

### Success criteria
- New-user activation rate (chat → accepted diff) > 60% in the first session.
- Time-to-first-meaningful-chat < 3 minutes from app open.

---

## Month 3 — Power-User Workflows

**Theme**: features the people who use it 4 hours/day will ask for.

### Deliverables
- **Dedicated review panel** for `/review` and `/test` results (Task #11). Structured findings list, jump-to-line, "fix this finding" button.
- **Persistent tool permissions** between sessions (Task #12). "Always allow `read_file` in this workspace" toggle.
- **Multi-root workspaces**: open more than one folder; indexer + chat operate over the union.
- **Diff history**: undo any agent-applied patch from a timeline view.
- **Custom slash commands**: `.llama-studio/commands/*.md` files in the repo define team-shared prompts.
- **MCP (Model Context Protocol) support**: connect external MCP servers as tools.

### Success criteria
- Power users report < 2 "fight the tool" moments per day.
- Custom commands adopted by at least one team in real use.

---

## Month 4 — Performance & Scale

**Theme**: feels fast on a 100k-LOC repo.

### Deliverables
- Incremental indexing: only re-embed changed files (already partial — finish + benchmark).
- Hotpath crate carries more weight: file tree walk, glob, ripgrep-style search moved off Python.
- Background indexing with progress UI + pause/resume.
- Streaming-chat load tests as a CI check (Task #13). p95 token-to-screen < 50ms under simulated load.
- Memory budget: agent sidecar < 250 MB resident for a 50k-LOC project; surface "indexer memory: N MB" in Settings.
- Lazy-load Monaco workers; first paint < 800ms cold.

### Success criteria
- Cold open → first chat on a 100k-LOC repo < 5 s.
- Indexing 100k LOC < 90 s on a mid-range laptop.

---

## Month 5 — Collaboration & Sharing

**Theme**: you're not alone in a tool anymore.

### Deliverables
- **Session export**: share a chat + diff as a single signed file (or paste-able URL via opt-in cloud gist).
- **Shared workspace profiles**: `.llama-studio/profile.toml` checked into a repo configures team defaults (model, allowed tools, slash commands, ignore patterns).
- **Pair mode** (experimental): two Zoc AI instances on the same LAN sync chat + cursor over WebRTC. Local-only, end-to-end encrypted.
- **GitHub / GitLab integration**: open a PR from an applied diff stack; pull a PR's diff into the review panel.
- **VS Code / JetBrains adapter** (read-only): show Zoc AI chat inside another editor.

### Success criteria
- A team can hand off a debugging session via a single shareable file.
- At least one open-source project ships a `.llama-studio/profile.toml`.

---

## Month 6 — Polish & Public Launch

**Theme**: ready for ProductHunt / HN.

### Deliverables
- Full design pass: empty states, error states, loading skeletons everywhere.
- Accessibility audit: keyboard-only navigation, screen-reader pass, color-contrast AA.
- Localization scaffold: en + es + zh + ja + de + fr; community-driven for the rest.
- Marketing site: <llama.studio> with feature pages, comparison table vs Cursor/Codex/Continue, 90-second demo video.
- Public Discord / GitHub Discussions, weekly office hours for the first month.
- v3.0.0 tag with everything above. Public launch.

### Success criteria
- 10k downloads in week 1.
- < 5% week-1 crash-free-session-rate regression vs internal builds.
- A community member ships their first PR within 30 days of launch.
